they have just
had the affirmation of the
country that they

16:15.875 --> 16:17.243 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are ready to lead.

16:17.276 --> 16:20.079 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they very quickly discover
how much they
don't know.

16:20.112 --> 16:25.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so I think that it was
interesting that
president-elect Trump today
talked about turning

16:25.284 --> 16:27.587 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to President Obama for counsel.

16:27.620 --> 16:32.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there's a long tradition of
that as well,
again, from former political
adversaries,

16:32.758 --> 16:39.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from people who don't share any
partisan views
in common, and yet recognize the
need to be

16:39.298 --> 16:42.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
talking to each other and the
resource that
former presidents can be.

16:42.768 --> 16:47.006 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, I suspect, you know,
president-elect Trump
would like to know that he can
call President

16:47.039 --> 16:49.709 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Obama in months to come when he
needs to.

16:49.742 --> 16:53.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think President Obama
would like to
know that that phone line is
open, as it has

16:53.679 --> 16:56.782 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
been in the past between sitting
presidents
and their predecessors.

16:56.816 --> 16:57.783 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JON MEACHAM: The real...

16:57.817 --> 16:58.784 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Jon Meacham, go
ahead.

16:58.818 --> 16:59.819 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JON MEACHAM: Sorry.

16:59.852 --> 17:03.122 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The real danger, as Nancy is
saying, is hubris.

17:03.155 --> 17:08.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And President Kennedy didn't
have -- Nancy
mentioned Eisenhower didn't
think much of

17:08.194 --> 17:10.129 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Kennedy.

17:10.162 --> 17:13.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, Kennedy didn't think much
of Eisenhower,
thought he was too bureaucratic,
the decision-making

17:13.099 --> 17:17.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was too militaristic, owed too
much to Eisenhower's
military command years.

17:17.870 --> 17:24.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kennedy comes in, wants a
freewheeling style,
empowers the CIA, empowers kind
of a more

17:24.343 --> 17:27.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
improvisational decision-making
world.

17:27.146 --> 17:30.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that led him to the Bay of
Pigs in April
of 1961.

17:30.583 --> 17:32.318 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And what does he do after that
disaster?

17:32.351 --> 17:37.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He picks up the phone and he
invites Dwight
Eisenhower to come to Camp
David, and they

17:37.623 --> 17:39.091 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
do it all again.

17:39.125 --> 17:42.762 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They sort of had -- they had to
have a second
transition to some extent.

17:42.795 --> 17:47.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I think that's the great
cautionary
example.

17:47.533 --> 17:50.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
These men need to listen to each
other and
learn quickly.

17:50.970 --> 17:54.240 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, what's for
sure is, all
eyes are on the two of them.

17:54.273 --> 17:56.909 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we thank both of you, Jon
Meacham, Nancy
Gibbs.

17:56.943 --> 17:59.812 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We appreciate it.

17:59.845 --> 18:09.121 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JON MEACHAM: Thanks, Judy.

18:09.155 --> 18:15.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: After that
